OL,3,CMan jailed for 14 years for 'violent,
OL,4,Cunprovoked' attack which killed dad
OL,6,F"You have caused terrible grief and
OL,7,Fimmeasurable pain that cannot be
OL,8,Fhealed.
OL,10,F"It is submitted on your behalf that
OL,11,Fyou feel remorse. You told your then
OL,12,Fprobation officer that you did not
OL,13,Fwant Mr Bradley to die, and you said
OL,14,Fyou were very emotional.
OL,16,F"You told the probation officer who
OL,17,Fwrote the pre-sentence report that you
OL,18,Ftook it too far, expressing regret for
OL,19,Fthe extent of your assault, but not
OL,20,Frecognising that you shouldn't have
OL,21,Fassaulted Mr Bradley at all.
